                <h1 class="h3 mt-3 mb-4 text-gray-800">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

                <h3>How do I upload my world to the Valheim server?</h3>
                <p>1. Start your game and join your server once (this will create your save folders)</p>
                <p>2. Locate the savegame files on your computer, usually stored at: C:\Users\username\AppData\LocalLow\IronGate\Valheim</p>
                <p>3. Grab the .db and .fwl file, then connect to your server using ftp with the credentials presented in your control panel (we recommend using Filezilla).</p>
                <p>4. Upload both files into this folder: /ftp/savedirectory/unity3d/IronGate/Valheim/worlds</p>
                <p>5. Go to the 2nd tab of the control panel and change the world name to the name of the files you just uploaded (if the file name is "example.db" you should type "example" into the world name box without the quotations).</p>
                <p>6. Click on save and restart server</p>
                <br>
                <h3>How do I make myself or others the admin(s) of my server? </h3>
                <p>Pressing f2 while in-game should display your username and steam64ID at the bottom. Copy and paste that number into adminlist.txt located at /ftp/savedirectory/unity3d/IronGate/Valheim/</p>
                <p>If you can't find your steam64ID in-game you can get it with the following method:</p>
                <p>1. Click on your username at the top right, then click on "view my profile". You should see a URL bar that displays: https://steamcommunity.com/profiles/[Long Number]/.
                    Copy and paste that number into adminlist.txt located at /ftp/savedirectory/unity3d/IronGate/Valheim/. If you don't see a URL bar, go to step 2.</p>
                <p>2. In your Steam client click on "View", then click on "Settings", then click on "Interface" on the left side.</p>
                <p>3. On the Interface page find  "Display Steam URL address bar when available", then click on the box next to it. Click on "Ok" to save the settings. Now you can go back to step 1.</p>
